criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion criteria:

          -  Diagnosis of advanced AIDS, defined as: CD4 count of less than 200 during the past 12
             months;

          -  On HAART for at least 6 months;

          -  Over age 18;

          -  Decisionally capable of providing informed consent.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  Not capable of providing informed consent because of psychiatric limitations, e.g.
             active psychosis.
